{
  "texts": [
    "Second, MetaGPT [58] found that frequent cooperation between agents can amplify minor hallucinations.",
    "To mitigate hallucinations, techniques such as cross-examination [133] or external supportive feedback [106] could improve the quality of agent output.",
    "Third, a single agent's error or misleading information can quickly spread to others, leading to flawed decisions or behaviors across the system.",
    "Pan et al. [123] established Open-Domain Question Answering Systems (ODQA) with and without propagated misinformation.",
    "They found that this propagation of errors can dramatically reduce the performance of the whole system."
  ]
}